6
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:16,729
(tires screeching)

7
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:18,348
(grunts)

8
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:21,770
(trumpets)

9
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:30,448
(croaking)

10
00:00:34,325 --> 00:00:37,075
{\an8}George, I'm sorry
to see you up here.

11
00:00:37,162 --> 00:00:40,122
{\an8}Well, yes, but I died
for a worthy cause.

12
00:00:40,206 --> 00:00:43,166
{\an8}As we speak, my body
is about to be dissected

13
00:00:43,251 --> 00:00:45,801
{\an8}by a budding
young scientist.

14
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:47,919
{\an8}Let's observe
the dedication to learning

15
00:00:48,006 --> 00:00:51,716
{\an8}of this ten-year-old scholar
by the name of Bart Simpson.

16
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:54,601
{\an8}♪ <i>Stab, stab, stab, stab,</i>
<i>stab, die</i> ♪

17
00:00:54,679 --> 00:00:56,719
{\an8}♪ <i>Stab, stab, die, die,</i>
<i>death, kill</i> ♪

18
00:00:56,806 --> 00:01:00,886
{\an8}Well, his passion
is undeniable.

19
00:01:00,977 --> 00:01:03,057
{\an8}Yes, very...
very impressive.

20
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:06,606
{\an8}By examining my specimen's
pyloric sphincter valve,

21
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:10,611
{\an8}I deduced that she had
an affinity for fruit flies.

22
00:01:10,695 --> 00:01:13,615
{\an8}By examining my specimen's
natty dreads,

23
00:01:13,698 --> 00:01:18,538
{\an8}I was able to deduce that he was
a jammin' Rasta-frogian.

24
00:01:18,620 --> 00:01:20,960
{\an8}My body,
my little green body.

25
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:23,629
{\an8}Okay, but surely
his portrayal

26
