{\an8}We be smokin' slabba-slabba
wit da Babylon.

29
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:34,392
{\an8}Ribbit, ribbit, mon.

30
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:36,809
{\an8}(panting loudly)

31
00:01:36,888 --> 00:01:38,308
{\an8}Come now, George.

32
00:01:38,389 --> 00:01:40,429
{\an8}At least this Scottish
groundskeeper

33
00:01:40,517 --> 00:01:42,687
{\an8}will give your remains
a respectful burial.

34
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:46,609
{\an8}WILLIE: Into the crapper you go,
useless froggy garbage.

35
00:01:46,689 --> 00:01:48,149
{\an8}(toilet flushing)

36
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:50,783
{\an8}Are you going to put
a good spin on that, too?

37
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:52,280
{\an8}Hmm? Are you?!

38
00:01:52,362 --> 00:01:53,452
{\an8}Well, are you?

39
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:56,830
{\an8}Well, uh... ribbit?

40
00:01:58,243 --> 00:02:00,753
{\an8}MARGE: I can't put these grades
on the refrigerator.

41
00:02:00,829 --> 00:02:03,209
{\an8}I can't even put them
on the garage refrigerator.

42
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:04,869
{\an8}It's not my fault.

43
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:06,918
{\an8}-I blame "so-key-ity."
-What?!

44
00:02:07,001 --> 00:02:08,631
You know, so-key-ity.

45
00:02:08,711 --> 00:02:11,091
That's what everyone
blames for everything.

46
00:02:11,172 --> 00:02:12,842
You mean "society"?

47
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:15,144
-Yeah, that's the guy.
-Honey,

48
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:16,928
I know you're a bright boy,

49
00:02:17,011 --> 00:02:19,141
but if you don't try harder
in school,

50
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:21,222
you could end up...

51
00:02:28,064 --> 00:02:30,074
...not a success.

52
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,070
Oh, that.
Don't worry, Mom.

53
00:02:32,152 --> 00:02:34,282
As long as I can stand on a corner

54
00:02:34,362 --> 00:02:35,992
and spin a sign reading "new condos,"

55
00:02:36,072 --> 00:02:38,072
I'll be just fine.

56
00:02:40,493 --> 00:02:42,253
(groaning)

57
00:02:42,328 --> 00:02:44,368
(Marge groaning)

58
00:02:46,749 --> 00:02:48,129
(Marge groaning)

59
00:02:48,209 --> 00:02:50,709
All that pacing
isn't gonna fix the boy.

60
00:02:50,795 --> 00:02:52,085
Just get him some pills.

61
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:54,422
Two pinks and a blue,
and it's off to the races.

62
00:02:54,507 --> 00:02:56,627
Everything we've tried
with Bart has failed.

63
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:58,638
What if there's nothing
we can do?

64
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,930
Mm, "nothing we can do"
is a whole lot better

65
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:02,474
than "it'll take all we've got."

66
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:06,477
I wonder if anyone talks
about parenting online.

67
00:03:09,397 --> 00:03:10,727
Look at this one!

68
00:03:10,815 --> 00:03:12,525
HOMER:
They're skiing.

69
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:14,149
Skiing means happy.

70
00:03:14,235 --> 00:03:17,065
Hmm, an expert with
a new book to promote.

71
00:03:17,155 --> 00:03:20,655
Oh, I wonder if she'd be willing
to speak to a group for a fee.

72
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:25,245
Getting your child established

73
00:03:25,330 --> 00:03:27,750
on the path to success
isn't easy.

74
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:30,632
I was driving my daughter
from her falconry tournament

75
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:33,170
to lute class
when she turned to me asked...

76
00:03:33,254 --> 00:03:34,714
(speaks Mandarin)

77
00:03:34,797 --> 00:03:37,587
...which is Mandarin for,
"How do you do it?"

78
00:03:37,675 --> 00:03:39,505
She and I are learning Mandarin.

79
00:03:39,594 --> 00:03:41,724
The answer?
(speaks Mandarin)

80
00:03:41,804 --> 00:03:43,514
Positive reinforcement.

81
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:45,518
(inquisitive chatter)

82
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:48,140
In a recent study,
this mouse was denied food

83
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:50,858
whenever he failed
to find his way through a maze.

84
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:54,029
The mouse ended up dying...
of low self-esteem.

85
00:03:54,108 --> 00:03:56,358
(shocked and excited chatter)

86
00:03:56,444 --> 00:03:58,704
I had a nightmare
where that happened to Bart,

87
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:00,700
but I never told you about it.

88
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:03,202
I love it when you
don't tell me things.

89
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:04,874
This mouse was given food

90
00:04:04,953 --> 00:04:07,123
whether he got
through the maze or not.

91
00:04:07,205 --> 00:04:10,535
And this fall,
he'll be in a lab at Harvard.

92
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:12,955
(excited gasps and chatter)

93
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:17,134
Low self-esteem can cripple
your child's chances of success.

94
00:04:17,215 --> 00:04:18,875
The cure: praise.

95
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:20,297
(excited chatter)

96
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:22,465
Praise they can hold
in their hands.

97
00:04:22,553 --> 00:04:26,143
Certificates, ribbons and, yes,
even trophies.

98
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:27,144
(crowd gasps)

99
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:28,725
(gasps) Trophies.

100
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:31,060
So that's the easy answer.

101
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:32,895
If Ralphie's shelf
says he's a winner,

102
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:34,571
then he'll be one!

103
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:37,779
And Moe yells a third thing
to feel part of the group!

104
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:42,492
Yes! Trophies--
that's what Bart needs.

105
00:04:42,573 --> 00:04:44,493
This is how we save him.

106
00:04:44,575 --> 00:04:46,785
(scoffs) Give Bart a trophy?
What for?

107
00:04:46,869 --> 00:04:49,079
Most boogers wiped
on a bedroom wall?

108
00:04:49,163 --> 00:04:51,123
They're giving trophies
for that now?

109
00:04:51,207 --> 00:04:52,827
I weep for this country.

110
00:04:52,917 --> 00:04:54,877
Bart's future is at stake.

111
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:57,131
Besides, I'm tired
of Springfield missing out

112
00:04:57,213 --> 00:05:01,553
on every parenting trend.
Like the time-out and the diaper.

113
00:05:01,634 --> 00:05:03,594
I never got a trophy
when I was a kid,

114
00:05:03,678 --> 00:05:05,308
and I turned out just...

115
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:07,388
(gulping)

116
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:14,314
(slowly)
...fine.

117
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:17,897
He's my son, and he's getting
a trophy for nothing.

118
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:20,404
You hear me?
For nothing!

119
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:23,985
Huh. Huh?

120
00:05:24,073 --> 00:05:24,953
(screams)

121
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:26,203
Good morning.

122
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:28,544
How's my special
little winner?

123
00:05:28,619 --> 00:05:31,329
How'd you get that thing
in my bed without waking me up?

124
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:33,794
Because you're
a champion sleeper.

125
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:35,875
It's the craziest thing.

126
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:38,210
She will not give up
on that kid.

127
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,836
Trophies <i>can </i>
boost self-esteem.

128
00:05:40,923 --> 00:05:43,263
If you actually win them,
like I did.

129
00:05:43,343 --> 00:05:44,553
But what's the point

130
00:05:44,635 --> 00:05:46,925
of just handing out
unearned statues?

131
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:48,433
And statuettes.

132
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:50,934
Well, it's just a waste
of gullible parents' money.

133
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:53,687
<i>(echoing) Waste of gullible</i>
<i>parents' money.</i>

134
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:55,940
<i>Gullible parents' money.</i>

135
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:57,772
<i>Money. Money.</i>

136
00:05:57,857 --> 00:05:59,567
-(bell dings)
-Hmm.

137
00:05:59,650 --> 00:06:01,900
Step right up!
Every kid's a winner!

138
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:04,406
The more you spend,
the more you love!

139
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:05,949
Mm-hmm.

140
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:10,949
I thought you agreed
that trophies should be earned.

141
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:13,287
I'm earning nature's
trophy: money.

142
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:14,293
(wind whistles softly)

143
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:15,464
Remember, folks.

144
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:18,091
Nothing but a genuine
Trophyland trophy says

145
00:06:18,169 --> 00:06:19,839
to your kids that...

146
