♪ <i>Nothing's gonna</i> ♪

154
00:06:37,271 --> 00:06:38,611
♪ <i>Ever keep you down</i> ♪

155
00:06:38,689 --> 00:06:41,399
♪ <i>You're the best around</i> ♪

156
00:06:41,484 --> 00:06:43,614
♪ <i>Nothing's gonna ever</i>
<i>keep you down</i> ♪

157
00:06:43,694 --> 00:06:46,164
♪ <i>You're the best</i> ♪

158
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:49,529
(chuckles) These stupid,
loving parents will buy trophies

159
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:51,657
for any accomplishment.

160
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:54,294
Not wetting the bed,
using your inside voice,

161
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:56,922
even "go watch TV
in the other room."

162
00:06:56,999 --> 00:07:00,089
I still think these things
are good for their self-esteem.

163
00:07:00,169 --> 00:07:01,749
Not to mention
the self-esteem

164
00:07:01,838 --> 00:07:04,168
that comes from
wad riffling.

165
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:05,167
(wind whistles softly)

166
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:07,638
Look, I even put the boy to work.

167
00:07:07,718 --> 00:07:10,428
Well, then he should get
a trophy for that.

168
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:11,763
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

169
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:14,268
We have a saying in
the participation trophy business.

170
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:16,390
"Don't get high--
self-esteem--

171
00:07:16,477 --> 00:07:18,597
on your own supply--
of self-esteem."

172
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:21,018
I don't care.
I'm giving him this.

173
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:22,817
What?
Why did it break?

174
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,530
The parts are of
the highest quality.

175
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:27,450
They come from
the China of China: India.

176
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:32,537
Boy, did you glue this trophy together
with bubblegum?

177
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:35,198
Eh, sticky is sticky.
I'm taking my break.

178
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:44,053
HOMER: See?
Giving him trophies did nothing.

179
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,670
You've showered him
with praise,

180
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:47,546
and he's just
as lazy as ever.

181
00:07:47,633 --> 00:07:49,723
Shh!
What if he heard you say that?

182
00:07:49,802 --> 00:07:52,262
Hey, if Bart is as bad
at eavesdropping

183
00:07:52,346 --> 00:07:54,016
as he is at everything else,

184
00:07:54,098 --> 00:07:56,098
we've got nothing
to worry about.

185
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:58,234
I say we keep
talking loudly.

186
00:07:58,311 --> 00:08:00,271
But what about
his confidence?

187
00:08:00,354 --> 00:08:02,694
Face it.
Our son is a screw-up.

188
00:08:02,773 --> 00:08:05,783
He was born a screw-up,
and no matter how hard he tries--

189
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:07,360
which he never will--

190
00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:09,775
Bart will <i>always </i>
be a screw-up.

191
00:08:09,864 --> 00:08:11,164
(groans)

192
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,950
And have you ever heard that sound
he makes when he's sad?

193
00:08:14,035 --> 00:08:15,495
Pathetic.

194
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:21,881
(sighs)

195
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:26,764
Queen's bishop Lomotil
takes king's Ativan.

196
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:29,049
Oh, looks like I'll be
having a panic attack

197
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:30,433
on the toilet tonight.

198
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:33,100
(scoffs) Look at that
whimpering little crybaby.

199
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:34,809
(mocking)
Wah! Wah!

200
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:37,389
Abe, that's your grandson.

201
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:38,805
Come visit me!

202
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:40,483
I'm so lonely!

203
00:08:40,561 --> 00:08:44,021
(crying)
Wah! Wah!

204
00:08:44,106 --> 00:08:45,976
What's got you down, kiddo?

205
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:48,437
My dad says I'm terrible
at everything.

206
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:51,408
Oh, he's just repeating
what he heard as a boy from me.

207
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:54,869
Oh, I was an awful father,
just like my old man.

208
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:56,621
Your dad didn't
believe in you, either?

209
00:08:56,702 --> 00:08:58,082
It wasn't his fault.

210
00:08:58,162 --> 00:09:00,622
He was just focused
on his career

211
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:03,076
as a professional child-beater.

212
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,037
<i>Men would come</i>
<i>from five towns over</i>

213
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:06,957
<i>to study my father's technique.</i>

214
00:09:07,046 --> 00:09:09,716
<i>But no matter</i>
<i>how many strangles he patented,</i>

215
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:12,129
<i>his father never approved.</i>

216
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:13,428
(choking loudly)

217
00:09:13,511 --> 00:09:16,431
Even if only a little bit
of that really happened,

218
00:09:16,514 --> 00:09:18,644
I'll never escape
being a loser.

219
00:09:18,724 --> 00:09:20,274
That's loser talk!

220
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:23,151
You're a great kid,
and I'm gonna prove it to you.

221
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:26,316
Boy, this here's a real trophy.

222
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:28,609
Our family's
most prized possession:

223
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:31,283
a Baumont Chrono-master Elite.

224
00:09:31,362 --> 00:09:32,782
It's been a Simpson heirloom

225
00:09:32,863 --> 00:09:35,993
ever since it was stolen
off a dead body at Gettysburg.

226
00:09:36,075 --> 00:09:37,735
In 1982.

227
00:09:37,827 --> 00:09:39,497
Whoa!

228
00:09:39,579 --> 00:09:42,079
Wait. Is this just another
gold shiny thing

229
00:09:42,164 --> 00:09:44,254
to trick me into
feeling special when I'm not?

230
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,543
You are special!

231
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:47,336
You're like my prostate--

232
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:50,720
a spiky little troublemaker
who plays by his own rules.

233
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:52,678
You don't take hooey
from Louie.

234
00:09:52,758 --> 00:09:54,678
Never have, never will.

235
00:09:57,179 --> 00:09:58,259
(shudders)

236
00:09:58,347 --> 00:09:59,887
I feel something.

237
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:02,104
It's like a sunburn
on the inside.

238
00:10:02,184 --> 00:10:03,394
It's called "pride."

239
00:10:03,477 --> 00:10:04,937
Every tick will remind you

240
00:10:05,021 --> 00:10:07,151
you've got a grandpa
who believes in you.

241
00:10:07,231 --> 00:10:08,771
The same way I believe

242
00:10:08,858 --> 00:10:11,938
the retirement home
has been taken over by robots.

243
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:13,738
(Eastern European accent)
I am not a robot.

244
00:10:13,821 --> 00:10:15,571
I just have
light-up sneakers.

